Great SRC sausage sizzle fundraiser today. Tasty!
Mr Riggs, soccer coaches and team managers are putting the final touches in place prior to the season kicking off next term. Not long now...
Remember the 2nd night of parent/ teacher interviews tonight. Feel free to call the office if you don't have the interview timetable handy
Btw, how good is the weather today!? It's been great seeing the kids in the sunshine. Tomorrow might be the last we see of Summer. Brrr...
13 days until the Yr 6/7's head to Canberra. Remember to set those alarm clocks nice and early for Sunday 10th...bus leaves @ 5:45am sharp!
I hope all Our Saviour people have had a wonderful (and perhaps indulgent?!) Christmas day. May Jesus' birth give you hope and love for 2011
Time is flying, last tweet was Easter and now the bells are almost jingling for Xmas. Can it be so? 11 school days after today....hold on!
Have a great break and a wonderful Easter with your family-a message to all Our Saviour students, parents and friends
Year 6/7's home from Mylor Camp safe & sound-giant swing (15m!), canoeing, raft making, bridge building, low ropes and even Red Faces. WOW!
Sleep well 6-7's...enjoying their first night at Mylor Camp. Enjoy the last days of Summer weather together
So good to see the kids back at Our Saviour today AND with so many new faces too!
HAPPY NEW YEAR to everyone at Our Saviour! Only 15 days until we see your smiling, excited faces again...we can't wait to HANG TEN IN 2010!
That's all folks. Merry Christmas to all of you-only 48 days until we're back for another great year together. God bless :-)
A fitting farewell for our graduating Yr 7's tonight. Is tomorrow really the last day of school? It's certainly been a sublime '09!
And if you hadn't noticed, there's a roof on our new building. On track for an April finish. Any ideas for the name for this new facility?
It's heating up outside but the kids are still smiling. Thankfully we only have one more day of this heat ;-)
Yes, the power is on tomorrow so the aircon will be firing on all cylinders. We'll stay as cool as we can
An encore performance of our whole school musical, The Rock Slinger & His Greatest Hit. What a final√© and what a team effort!!!
As if you've had time to catch your breath-this Thu & Fri is our whole-school musical. 7pm @ the Church
Spring Fair '09 was a great success for Our Saviour: approx $15,000 raised and a wonderful celebration of our school community
And YES, Principal, Pastor and teachers will all be on the dunking machine. Ready, aim...
Yes, there's just one sleep until the much-awaited Spring Fair. 9am-3pm @ 28 Taylors Road West, Aberfoyle Park. See you there!
5 sleeps till the Our Saviour Spring Fair!
Now it's on the road again for home sweet home. Keith Bakery for lunch on the way-see you soon!!!
A trip to the Nelson beach yesterday afternoon, a scrumptious roast for our last pub meal and then an early night.
Glenelg River boat cruise this morning. Another sunny day...will they be able to drag us home?
Sausage sizzle @ Valley Lake then a climb up Mt Schank...and then down into the volcano. Back to camp for relaxing and Red Faces rehearsals
Just coming into Mt Gambier after a big sleep and a slow start to the morning. A lap and aquifer tour @ the Blue Lake to get us going
Macca's as a reward and now back to Nelson Pub for fish and chips. What a way to end our day. Off to Mt Gambier in the morning
59 soft serves @ Warrnambool
59 resilient, supportive and inspirational students have just finished walking 25km from Pt Fairy to Warrnambool. We are so proud of them!!!
Naracoorte Caves great, Karnkendi Camp fantastic, Nelson pub schnitzel delicious, good sleep. About to start 25km trek...
Just passed through the Heysen Tunnels and it's all smooth sailing. Dare I say it, the kids are perfect!
If you're in Yr 5-7, go to bed! A MASSIVE weeks awaits us all as we leave Our Saviour @ 7:30am sharp for an intrepid journey to Nelson  :-)
Assembly & Worship @ 1:30pm today. Please join us as we finish our terrific Term 3 together. Have a great break, see you on Tue 13th Oct
And now it's time to head back...a supreme Sinai Survivor and the kids have been fantastic company.
Marshmallows and witchetty grubs for supper, a good night's sleep (until 5:30am!), some exploring and enjoying the sunny Spring day.
On the home stretch now, the sun is shining, we can almost smell the sea air...and the pizza. And we're all still smiling!
Time for lunch. Highlights of the day = Josh's shoe falling off in a slippery cow pat and Nikki doing a sensational slide on her backside.
Just started the Sinai Survivor with 18 adventurous Yr 7's. A 25km journey begins with a single step.
Cont... Afternoon with our Grandfriends too-how special they are to us all :-)
The kids looked fantastic in their hunter and animal costumes...and what about that gorilla on the library roof!? It was great to spend the
What a Wednesday! There's Book Week celebrations and Grandfriends Day too. We can't wait to see all the kids dressed up as jungle creatures.
SAPSASA Athletics team off to Santos Stadium today. Run, jump and throw your very best.
Just heard from Mrs Skinner that we received Honours @ the Tournament of Minds presentation. Well done and HOORAY!!!
